00:25:38,847 --> 00:25:41,600
to comply with our comic book code.

472
00:25:41,684 --> 00:25:44,312
You are, at the moment, the only holdouts.

473
00:25:44,896 --> 00:25:47,650
If you do not abide by our strictures,

474
00:25:47,733 --> 00:25:49,862
then you will not be able to print

475
00:25:49,945 --> 00:25:52,698
the comic book code
seal of approval on your books.

476
00:25:52,781 --> 00:25:54,450
No. No.

477
00:25:54,534 --> 00:25:55,869
Not even <i>Super Duck.</i>

478
00:25:55,952 --> 00:26:02,669
Which means that no newsstand in America
will sell or even carry your comic books.

479
00:26:02,752 --> 00:26:05,548
They will be relegated to the trash heap.

480
00:26:07,301 --> 00:26:08,385
Where they belong.

481
00:26:13,809 --> 00:26:15,519
I know it's been a busy week,

482
00:26:15,603 --> 00:26:17,606
but did you all have
a chance to read "Howl"?

483
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:21,152
Good, let's open it up for discussion.

484
00:26:21,235 --> 00:26:22,737
What did you all think?

485
00:26:22,820 --> 00:26:25,032
Dynamic and hallucinogenic.

486
00:26:25,115 --> 00:26:28,703
A subterranean toppling of idolatry,
and an awakening.

487
00:26:29,454 --> 00:26:31,790
Very good, Clay. Archie.

488
00:26:32,583 --> 00:26:34,586
What did you think of Ginsberg's poem?

489
00:26:34,669 --> 00:26:35,754
I...

490
00:26:37,590 --> 00:26:39,927
couldn't sleep after reading it.

491
00:26:41,803 --> 00:26:44,057
Where does a humdinger like "Howl"
even come from?

492
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,810
Well, Allen's lived a lot of life.

493
00:26:46,894 --> 00:26:52,067
My husband says you can't be a real poet
without really living.

494
00:26:52,150 --> 00:26:53,569
Well, in that case...

495
00:26:54,195 --> 00:26:57,032
I'm never gonna be able
to write anything like "Howl."

496
00:26:57,115 --> 00:26:59,076
Why would you say that, Archie?

497
00:26:59,159 --> 00:27:00,745
Because look at me, Mrs. Grundy.

498
00:27:00,828 --> 00:27:03,122
I'm a square. What am I gonna write about?

499
00:27:03,206 --> 00:27:06,043
Jack Kerouac played football
in small-town Massachusetts

500
00:27:06,126 --> 00:27:08,630
before going to Columbia to study writing.

501
00:27:08,713 --> 00:27:12,093
Maybe it's more about
keeping an open mind about things.

502
00:27:12,176 --> 00:27:17,350
Being open to trying new things
with different people.

503
00:27:18,226 --> 00:27:21,146
Or more than one person.

504
00:27:21,230 --> 00:27:22,064
Maybe two.

505
00:27:22,940 --> 00:27:24,818
Let me ask you this, Archie.

506
00:27:25,735 --> 00:27:27,655
Have you ever seen the sunrise?

507
00:27:28,239 --> 00:27:29,156
Sure.

508
00:27:29,240 --> 00:27:31,660
You mean like waking up early
for basketball practice?

509
00:27:31,743 --> 00:27:33,955
No, no, I mean, staying up all night.

510
00:27:34,872 --> 00:27:36,499
With your friends, drinking coffee,

511
00:27:36,582 --> 00:27:40,380
and getting into
deep philosophical conversations

512
00:27:40,463 --> 00:27:45,928
that last until the sky streaks pink
and yellow with the dawn's early light.

513
00:27:46,012 --> 00:27:48,307
My husband and I do that once a month.

514
00:27:49,976 --> 00:27:51,602
Let me tell you, it is...

515
00:27:52,895 --> 00:27:54,023
transcendent.

516
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:57,569
It's like being reborn.

517
00:27:59,321 --> 00:28:01,991
Betty, what's your take on "Howl"?

518
00:28:02,074 --> 00:28:06,121
To be honest, Mrs. Grundy,
I'm halfway through it, and...

519
00:28:08,666 --> 00:28:10,461
so far I...

520
00:28:11,295 --> 00:28:12,880
appreciate how...

521
00:28:12,963 --> 00:28:16,761
How it isn't afraid
to ask the hard questions?

522
00:28:16,844 --> 00:28:19,305
To have the difficult conversations

523
00:28:19,388 --> 00:28:23,101
that many of us
are too afraid to even begin?

524
00:28:25,688 --> 00:28:26,690
[DOOR CLOSES]

525
00:28:34,909 --> 00:28:36,285
<i>Lady's Leisure?</i>

526
00:28:37,537 --> 00:28:39,206
Any interesting articles?

527
00:28:39,289 --> 00:28:41,417
What can I do for you, Elizabeth?

528
00:28:42,168 --> 00:28:44,129
I came here to see if you wanted

529
00:28:44,213 --> 00:28:46,925
to join me and my gal pals
tonight at the Babylonium.

530
00:28:47,008 --> 00:28:47,884
Oh.

531
00:28:49,511 --> 00:28:51,013
Polly's performing.

532
00:28:52,932 --> 00:28:53,767
What?

533
00:28:54,810 --> 00:28:56,269
Polly's here?

534
00:28:56,353 --> 00:28:57,271
In Riverdale?

535
00:28:57,355 --> 00:28:58,606
And she's performing?

536
00:28:58,690 --> 00:29:00,567
She is. I called her.

537
00:29:02,236 --> 00:29:03,905
When were you planning on telling me

538
00:29:03,988 --> 00:29:06,449
that my sister
is world-famous burlesque dancer?

539
00:29:06,533 --> 00:29:08,828
Never, if I had my druthers.

540
00:29:10,789 --> 00:29:14,252
So is that why you've been
so down on me all this time?

541
00:29:14,335 --> 00:29:17,381
Are you punishing me for Polly's choices

542
00:29:17,464 --> 00:29:20,218
or trying to make sure
that I don't follow in her footsteps?

543
00:29:21,136 --> 00:29:23,096
Can't believe
your sister's here performing.

544
00:29:23,179 --> 00:29:24,682
Well, she is.

545
00:29:24,765 --> 00:29:29,938
She's living her life, Mom, without us,
because you decided to cut her off.

546
00:29:31,107 --> 00:29:33,151
Did you know that she's engaged?

547
00:29:34,319 --> 00:29:35,696
To a stock broker.

548
00:29:37,490 --> 00:29:39,117
Don't you wanna go to her wedding?

549
00:29:39,701 --> 00:29:42,246
Please just come to the show tonight, Mom.

550
00:29:42,329 --> 00:29:46,251
Imagine what a great surprise
that it would be for her,

551
00:29:46,334 --> 00:29:51,925
not to mention the best chance
we have to just be a family again.

552
00:29:52,009 --> 00:29:56,055
In what world would I wanna go
and watch my daughter

553
00:29:56,139 --> 00:29:58,225
debase herself for dirty old men?

554
00:29:58,309 --> 00:30:01,646
It is not for dirty old men.
It is just for girls.

555
00:30:01,730 --> 00:30:03,900
Well, I don't care
if it's for the Virgin Mary.

556
00:30:05,193 --> 00:30:06,277
Well, I'm going.

557
00:30:07,488 --> 00:30:09,782
And don't even try to forbid me,

558
00:30:09,865 --> 00:30:12,702
because I'm proud of Polly,

559
00:30:12,786 --> 00:30:14,789
and I want to support her,

560
00:30:14,872 --> 00:30:18,293
and show her that I love
and accept her no matter what.

561
00:30:19,461 --> 00:30:20,713
Unlike her mother.

562
00:30:27,472 --> 00:30:28,640
You ready?

563
00:30:28,723 --> 00:30:29,557
Ready.

564
00:30:33,855 --> 00:30:34,689
[REGGIE] Yeah.

565
00:30:53,881 --> 00:30:55,216
What? No.

566
00:30:56,175 --> 00:30:57,886
No, no, no.

567
00:30:57,970 --> 00:30:59,179
No! No!

568
00:30:59,263 --> 00:31:01,015
What are we supposed to do now?

569
00:31:01,099 --> 00:31:02,934
I'm horny as heck.

570
00:31:05,271 --> 00:31:06,313
Me too, Reg.

571
00:31:07,190 --> 00:31:08,275
Me too.

572
00:31:09,860 --> 00:31:10,695
Wait.

573
00:31:13,406 --> 00:31:14,575
I got an idea.

574
00:31:16,743 --> 00:31:19,873
Now, it's a little raunchy,
but, I mean, if you're up for it...

575
00:31:27,550 --> 00:31:29,385
["DIAMONDS AND PEARLS" PLAYING]

576
00:31:35,143 --> 00:31:36,853
Well, well, well.

577
00:31:37,813 --> 00:31:39,982
Looks like Twyla hit the jackpot tonight.

578
00:31:41,401 --> 00:31:43,738
Now, which one of you hunks
of Wisconsin man cheese

579
00:31:43,821 --> 00:31:45,156
is coming in first?

580
00:31:46,782 --> 00:31:51,372
Or maybe you both wanna come in
at the same time?

581
00:31:52,832 --> 00:31:54,835
[WHIMSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

582
00:32:11,190 --> 00:32:13,233
[WOMEN SHOUTING AND CHEERING]

583
00:32:13,317 --> 00:32:15,028
