<i>♪ For me ♪</i>

626
00:34:33,332 --> 00:34:34,292
<i>♪ For me ♪</i>

627
00:34:37,213 --> 00:34:44,222
<i>♪ For me ♪</i>

628
00:34:49,478 --> 00:34:51,022
[CHEERING]

629
00:34:58,448 --> 00:35:01,911
Polly, that was spectacular.

630
00:35:01,995 --> 00:35:03,580
Oh, it was okay.

631
00:35:03,663 --> 00:35:05,499
Still working out the kinks.

632
00:35:05,583 --> 00:35:07,001
Well, some of them.

633
00:35:07,084 --> 00:35:11,591
I'm just glad I finally got to see
a bona fide burlesque star in the flesh.

634
00:35:11,674 --> 00:35:14,678
But interestingly, not too much flesh.

635
00:35:14,761 --> 00:35:16,013
Well, that is correct.

636
00:35:16,096 --> 00:35:18,766
If you're good enough,
you can suggest more than show.

637
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:22,605
Well, you, my dear Ms. Amorous,
are better than good.

638
00:35:23,355 --> 00:35:26,902
I'm just sorry that Mom didn't come.
I really thought that she might rally.

639
00:35:26,985 --> 00:35:28,321
Oh, it's okay.

640
00:35:28,404 --> 00:35:30,406
She doesn't believe in what I do.

641
00:35:30,489 --> 00:35:33,160
But that's on her, not me or you.

642
00:35:33,827 --> 00:35:38,083
But, Betty, if you take
anything from my visit, let it be this.

643
00:35:38,167 --> 00:35:43,131
When you find the thing that you love,
just promise me that you'll do it.

644
00:35:43,215 --> 00:35:46,552
No matter what Mom or anybody says.

645
00:35:46,636 --> 00:35:47,554
I promise.

646
00:35:48,889 --> 00:35:49,973
And...

647
00:35:50,975 --> 00:35:54,104
I want nothing more
than to be your maid of honor.

648
00:35:54,188 --> 00:35:55,564
[POLLY] Oh, Betty.

649
00:35:57,107 --> 00:35:59,277
Oh. Consider yourself booked.

650
00:36:09,249 --> 00:36:10,250
Wow.

651
00:36:11,585 --> 00:36:13,295
Mrs. Grundy was right.

652
00:36:15,382 --> 00:36:18,010
Staying up all night
really does make the dawn look...

653
00:36:18,094 --> 00:36:20,096
Different somehow.

654
00:36:20,931 --> 00:36:21,932
Yeah.

655
00:36:25,311 --> 00:36:26,604
And now that we've...

656
00:36:30,484 --> 00:36:34,323
expanded our horizons...

657
00:36:34,407 --> 00:36:35,574
It seems like...

658
00:36:36,492 --> 00:36:38,537
anything's possible at this point.

659
00:36:45,879 --> 00:36:48,133
I love you, Reggie.

660
00:36:49,926 --> 00:36:51,304
I love you too, bud.

661
00:37:01,525 --> 00:37:03,527
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

662
00:37:14,500 --> 00:37:16,836
Sweetheart, something wrong?

663
00:37:16,919 --> 00:37:19,757
Perhaps you should pray on it
in the chapel.

664
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:27,058
I don't get to go as often as I'd like,
but when I do, I find such comfort there.

665
00:37:28,060 --> 00:37:28,935
[SCOFFS]

666
00:37:30,562 --> 00:37:32,523
Toni, I have a question for you.

667
00:37:32,607 --> 00:37:35,194
Do you still have the negatives
from our photo shoot?

668
00:37:35,277 --> 00:37:36,570
Of course.

669
00:37:36,653 --> 00:37:37,655
Why?

670
00:37:37,739 --> 00:37:41,744
My hideous mother,
and by extension, my father...

671
00:37:43,037 --> 00:37:45,123
I can't keep living at their mercy.

672
00:37:45,207 --> 00:37:48,127
I wanna shut them up and shut them down.

673
00:37:48,211 --> 00:37:50,421
Once and for all.

674
00:37:55,762 --> 00:37:57,263
Didn't hear you come in last night.

675
00:37:59,475 --> 00:38:02,896
I presume Polly's on her way
back to New York City?

676
00:38:02,979 --> 00:38:04,190
- Yes.
- [ALICE SIGHS]

677
00:38:05,358 --> 00:38:06,692
And I'm so jealous.

678
00:38:06,776 --> 00:38:07,861
She has...

679
00:38:08,779 --> 00:38:10,155
freedom,

680
00:38:10,739 --> 00:38:13,660
a career she loves,
someone in her life who worships her.

681
00:38:13,743 --> 00:38:16,038
That's more
than any one of us here can say.

682
00:38:16,122 --> 00:38:18,750
Don't pick a fight with me, Elizabeth.
I'm not in the mood.

683
00:38:18,834 --> 00:38:21,045
So when are you going to stop?

684
00:38:22,964 --> 00:38:25,592
Stop sabotaging our family?

685
00:38:25,676 --> 00:38:27,762
- Oh, is that what you think I'm doing?
- Isn't it?

686
00:38:27,846 --> 00:38:31,976
Did you forget
when you disowned me as your daughter?

687
00:38:32,059 --> 00:38:34,479
You drove Polly away.

688
00:38:34,563 --> 00:38:38,067
We couldn't even have one night together,
the three of us,

689
00:38:38,151 --> 00:38:39,652
because of your hang-ups.

690
00:38:39,735 --> 00:38:44,367
You know what?
You are a sad, lonely woman.

691
00:38:44,451 --> 00:38:46,744
And it is all your own doing.

692
00:38:46,828 --> 00:38:48,038
But I'll tell you this, Mom.

693
00:38:48,122 --> 00:38:50,791
I am not giving you
any more power over my life

694
00:38:50,875 --> 00:38:52,794
because you will ruin it.

695
00:38:52,878 --> 00:38:54,881
I'm going to do exactly what Polly did,

696
00:38:54,964 --> 00:38:57,425
and the second I can leave this town,
I'm gone.

697
00:38:57,508 --> 00:38:58,844
Fine.

698
00:38:58,927 --> 00:39:00,053
Go!

699
00:39:00,137 --> 00:39:01,014
Oh.

700
00:39:01,931 --> 00:39:03,266
You should know, after last night,

701
00:39:03,349 --> 00:39:05,102
I'm thinking of following
in Polly's footsteps

702
00:39:05,186 --> 00:39:06,896
and becoming a burlesque dancer too.

703
00:39:06,979 --> 00:39:09,983
Except maybe I'll take off all my clothes.

704
00:39:10,066 --> 00:39:11,819
And then what will you tell your friends?

705
00:39:11,903 --> 00:39:14,406
Or will you just pretend
that I don't exist

706
00:39:14,490 --> 00:39:16,033
or that I died tragically?

707
00:39:16,116 --> 00:39:17,619
- Elizabeth...
- It doesn't matter.

708
00:39:17,702 --> 00:39:20,914
Because I won't be in this house.
I'll be far away from you,

709
00:39:20,998 --> 00:39:24,001
doing whatever I want,
and you can't stop me.

710
00:39:29,342 --> 00:39:31,345
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

711
00:39:36,142 --> 00:39:37,143
[SOBBING]

712
00:39:45,488 --> 00:39:48,242
I'm surprised
it took you this long to do that.

713
00:39:55,459 --> 00:39:56,919
[VERONICA] So, what happens now?

714
00:39:58,129 --> 00:40:01,384
Well, if we don't follow their code,

715
00:40:01,467 --> 00:40:04,388
we can't publish our comics
with their seal of approval.

716
00:40:04,471 --> 00:40:08,268
And if we can't get that,
then publishers won't print our comics,

717
00:40:08,351 --> 00:40:12,106
distributors will not ship them,
and newsstands will not sell them.

718
00:40:12,189 --> 00:40:17,905
So we either follow their cockeyed rules
or we go the way of the dodos.

719
00:40:20,449 --> 00:40:22,202
How can I have been so naïve?

720
00:40:23,829 --> 00:40:28,377
I really thought
that there was a way through this.

721
00:40:28,460 --> 00:40:30,838
